{"word":"H567 - אֱמֹרִי - ʼĔmôrîy - em-o-ree' - Amorite","slug":"H567","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אֱמֹרִי</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼĔmôrîy"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>em-o-ree'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Amorite"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05DE;&#x05E8;&#x05D9; - 'e&#x0306;mo&#x0302;r&#x0131;&#x0302;y</b> - <i>em-o-ree'</i><p/>Probably a patronymic from an unused name derived from <a href=\"#/H559\">H559</a> in the sense of <i>publicity</i>, that is, prominence; thus a <i>mountaineer</i>; an <i>Emorite</i>, one of the Canaanitish tribes: - Amorite."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H201\">H201</a>, <a href=\"#/H204\">H204</a>, <a href=\"#/H3982\">H3982</a>, <a href=\"#/H534\">H534</a>, <a href=\"#/H559\">H559</a>, <a href=\"#/H561\">H561</a>, <a href=\"#/H562\">H562</a>, <a href=\"#/H564\">H564</a>, <a href=\"#/H565\">H565</a>, <a href=\"#/H566\">H566</a>, <a href=\"#/H568\">H568</a>, <a href=\"#/H569\">H569</a>, <a href=\"#/H570\">H570</a>, <a href=\"#/H577\">H577</a>"}]}